pageContext.claim: “That was an oppo research meeting. And I would say that everybody in Washington has had those meetings. You know, your opponent -- 'hey, we have information on your opponent. Would you like to hear?' I mean, you tell me how many politicians would turn that meeting down. And then it turned out she did that -- it turned out you didn't have any information.”
pageContext.analysis: Ethics lawyers and campaign veterans say the sort of encounter between Donald Trump Jr. and the Russian attorney at the Trump Tower is highly unusual.
